title: Stegmaier leads suspended Shriners Open
text: Stegmaier leads suspended Shriners Open Saturday, 24 October 2015 (17 minutes ago) Brett Stegmaier was clinging to a one-shot lead with three holes to play on Friday when darkness stopped the second round of the Shriners Hospitals for Children Open. Brett Stegmaier topped the leaderboard Friday in the Shriners Hospitals for Children Open in only his fifth career start on the PGA Tour. Recent related news Stegmaier is at 11 under overall; second-round play is suspended because of darkness.
